Use `async/await` with `next(err)` only for forwarding errors; keep the same order and minimal flow:

```js
async function loadUser(req, res, next) {
  try {
    const user = await User.findById(req.params.id);
    req.user = user;
    next();
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
}
```

